history.content:
16AB are designed with L&S intended-CS students very much in mind. (As long as you have a 5 on the Calc BC AP exam or equivalent) It's only because of the backlog of demand that it has been nearly impossible for them to get in till next semester. 

We are hoping to have some seats available for L&S intended-CS freshmen in 16A in Spring. The Fall offering was super impacted and we were sadly unable to let more than a handful of intended-CS freshmen into the course --- or for that matter, even declared CS students. The Spring offering is both bigger and we expect that most of the pent-up EECS demand will already have been satisfied in Fall. So, quite a few seats should be available for L&S students. 

However, our initial estimates say that 16A in the Spring might still be oversubscribed and because of lab-space limits, the size can't grow significantly beyond what is on the schedule. So if you are L&S intended-CS, be sure to keep that in mind.

Does the EECS Department believe that for Spring 2016, EE 16A will be able to accomodate for freshman in L&S CS? Also, will there be spots reserved for L&S CS Majors (or undeclared) for EE 16A since it is a lower division requirement for the CS major?
history.subject: EE16A for LS CS Freshman
